STATE of Missouri, Respondent,
v.
William J. BARTLETT, Appellant. WD 80451 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: April 9, 2019 Christian Lehmberg, Columbia, MO, Counsel for Appellant. Julia Rives, Jefferson City, MO, Counsel for Respondent. Before Division One: Cynthia L. Martin, P.J., Victor C. Howard, and Thomas H. Newton, JJ.

ORDER

Per Curiam:

Mr. William J. Bartlett appeals a Buchanan County Circuit Court conviction of second-degree child molestation following a jury trial. Mr. Bartlett was sentenced to one year in county jail and was ordered to register as a sex offender. For reasons stated in the memorandum provided to the parties, we affirm. Rule 30.25(b).
